      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a collector-grade example of Bavarian engineering, featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six engine with individual throttle bodies and a 7,900 RPM redline. Power is sent to the rear wheels via a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M differential lock. This vehicle has undergone rigorous preventative maintenance, including a reinforced rear subframe and rod bearing replacement. The suspension geometry remains true to factory specifications, providing the sharp turn-in and telepathic feedback these chassis are known for. The exterior retains its original deep luster, and the interior is free of bolster wear or pixel degradation in the instrument cluster. Mechanically pristine and aesthetically flawless, this M3 is a turn-key investment for the serious driver.",
